      <description><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/655184915_18087851819521202_3402786512315793323_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=101&amp;ig_cache_key=Mzg1NzA2MjQwMjIyMzUxMDczOA%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjExMDR4MTQ3Mi5zZHIuQzMifQ%3D%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=BXju0LTaxcgQ7kNvwGthAaQ&amp;_nc_oc=Adp6JmMcBUCrLABQuHjIBnV-q_zTwgsfoAmO1pQBe7gFJfaOL9aRFX42H4UIeQJPT9U&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;se=7&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=zN_JptTc3nfT0ay_MwZSlQ&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_AfzijkUIwcCbBuPPQOgWNWbOXfkPGKl_4UIhkdtxgWO0Vw&amp;oe=69CA0E69" alt="Instagram billede fra @lias_saoudi" /></p><p><strong>@lias_saoudi</strong></p><p>⭐️FESTIVAL SPOTLIGHT ⭐️<br/>
<br/>
Join us to hear Daniel Dylan Wray in conversation about Groovy, Laidback and Nasty. Daniel will be in conversation with Lias Saoudi from Fat White Family. This event is brought to you in collaboration with White Rabbit Books.<br/>
<br/>
From dazzling electronic futurism to pioneering post-punk, via pop, metal, bassline, bleep techno and generation-defining indie rock, Sheffield has long been a crucible for world-leading music.<br/>
<br/>
In Groovy, Laidback and Nasty, acclaimed Sheffield journalist, Daniel Dylan Wray, sets out to remedy this, telling the story of the city’s DIY spirit and the musical visionaries and innovators who helped build its inimitable legacy. Brilliantly researched and spanning almost seven decades, it features over 150 interviews with the likes of Pulp, Arctic Monkeys, The Human League, Cabaret Voltaire, Self Esteem and Richard Hawley.<br/>
<br/>
Tickets available at www.theheathbookshop.co.uk<br/>
<br/>
This event will be BSL interpreted.<br/>
<br/>
The Heath Bookshop Literature and Music Festival is supported by National Lottery Project Grants funding through Arts Council England.<br/>
<br/>
@hareandhoundsbrum</p>]]></description>
